  "subject": "Docs: Migrate seqdiag diagrams to Mermaid",
  "commit_message": "Docs: Migrate seqdiag diagrams to Mermaid\n\nConvert all 4 seqdiag sequence diagrams (publishAnyEvent and\npublishEventBatch call flows in both VES 7.1 and VES 7.2 specs)\nfrom sphinxcontrib-seqdiag to sphinxcontrib-mermaid.\n\nThe seqdiag extension was already removed from conf.py and\nrequirements-docs.txt in a prior change; this commit converts the\nremaining live directives in the RST content.\n\nChanges:\n- docs/Chapter8/ves7_1spec.rst: 2 seqdiag -> mermaid sequenceDiagram\n- docs/Chapter8/ves_7_2/ves_event_listener_7_2.rst: 2 seqdiag -> mermaid\n- tox.ini: Pin basepython to python3.13\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: I0e727b0d5288ea3dd00db637c9f4cd6c3aeab5c7\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
